label: agency_id
comment: ID that uniquely identifies a transit agency. A transit feed may represent data from more than one agency. The agency_id is dataset unique. This field is optional for transit feeds that only contain data for a single agency. SameAs: 'agency_id' field from GTFS Static Field Definition - agency.txt (https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs/reference#agencytxt)

label: agency_name
comment: The agency_name field contains the full name of the transit agency. SameAs: 'agency_name' field from GTFS Static Field Definition - agency.txt (https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs/reference#agencytxt)

label: agency_url
comment: The agency_url field contains the URL of the transit agency. SameAs: 'agency_url' field from GTFS Static Field Definition - agency.txt (https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs/reference#agencytxt)

label: agency_timezone
comment: Timezone field contains the timezone where the transit agency is located. SameAs: 'agency_timezone' field from GTFS Static Field Definition - agency.txt (https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs/reference#agencytxt)

label: agency_lang
comment: Contains a two-letter ISO 639-1 code for the primary language used by this transit agency. The language code is case-insensitive (both en and EN are accepted). SameAs: 'agency_lang' field from GTFS Static Field Definition - agency.txt (https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs/reference#agencytxt)

label: route_id
comment: Route ID assigned to the route on which the bus/vehicle corresponding to the bus in this observation is currently plying on. SameAs: 'route_id' field from GTFS Realtime message-TripDescriptor https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs-realtime/reference#message-tripdescriptor

label: route_short_name
comment: Short name of a route. This will often be the transit vehicle's board name like "402D", or "Green" that riders use to identify a route. SameAs: 'route_short_name' field from GTFS Static Field definitions-routes.txt https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs/reference#routestxt

label: route_long_name
comment: Full name of a route. This name is more descriptive than the routeShortName and often includes the route's destination or stop. This mostly includes the to and from destination names of the route. SameAs: 'route_long_name' field from GTFS Static Field definitions-routes.txt https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs/reference#routestxt

label: route_desc
comment: Description of the route. This can include the entire route details including to and from destination and timing information in a text description form. SameAs: 'route_desc' field from GTFS Static Field definitions-routes.txt https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs/reference#routestxt

label: route_type
comment: Number indicating the type of transport- 1 - Subway, Metro. Any underground rail system within a metropolitan area. 2 - Rail. Used for intercity or long-distance travel. 3 - Bus. Used for short- and long-distance bus routes. SameAs: 'route_type' field from GTFS Static Field definitions-routes.txt https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs/reference#routestxt

label: route_url
comment: Contains the URL of a web page about that particular route and is different from the agency_url. SameAs: 'route_url' field from GTFS Static Field definitions-routes.txt (https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs/reference#routestxt)

label: route_color
comment: If assigned, this field defines a color that corresponds to a route. The color must be provided as a six-character hexadecimal number, for example, 00FFFF. If no color is specified, the default route color is white (FFFFFF). SameAs: 'route_color' field from GTFS Static Field definitions-routes.txt (https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs/reference#routestxt)

label: route_text_color
comment: This field can be used to specify a legible color to use for text drawn against a background of route_color. The color must be provided as a six-character hexadecimal number, for example, FFD700. If no color is specified, the default text color is black (000000). SameAs: 'route_text_color' field from GTFS Static Field definitions-routes.txt (https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs/reference#routestxt)

label: stop_name
comment: Describes the name of a stop or station. SameAs: 'stop_name' field from GTFS Static Field definitions-stops.txt (https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs/reference#stopstxt)

label: stop_code
comment: This field contains short text or a number that uniquely identifies the stop for passengers. Can be same as stop_id if it is for public. SameAs: 'stop_code' field from GTFS Static Field definitions-stops.txt (https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs/reference#stopstxt)

label: stop_desc
comment: This field contains a description of a stop. SameAs: 'stop_desc' field from GTFS Static Field definitions-stops.txt (https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs/reference#stopstxt)

label: stop_lat
comment: This field contains the latitude of a stop or station. SameAs: 'stop_lat' field from GTFS Static Field definitions-stops.txt (https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs/reference#stopstxt)

label: stop_lon
comment: This field contains the longitude of a stop or station. SameAs: 'stop_lon' field from GTFS Static Field definitions-stops.txt (https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs/reference#stopstxt)

label: zone_id
comment: This field defines the fare zone for a stop ID. SameAs: 'zone_id' field from GTFS Static Field definitions-stops.txt (https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs/reference#stopstxt)

label: stop_url
comment: This field contains the URL of a web page about a particular stop and is different from the agency_url and the route_url fields. SameAs: 'stop_url' field from GTFS Static Field definitions-stops.txt (https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs/reference#stopstxt)

label: route_id
comment: Route ID assigned to the route on which the bus/vehicle corresponding to the bus in this observation is currently plying on. SameAs: 'route_id' field from GTFS Realtime message-TripDescriptor (https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs-realtime/reference#message-tripdescriptor)

label: stop_sequence_detail
comment: Describes the stop sequence for a trip in the designated route made by the public transit vehicle. SameAs: 'stop_sequence' field from GTFS Static Field definitions-stop_times.txt (https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs/reference#stop_timestxt)

label: stop_id
comment: Stop ID/Stop name of the bus stops corresponding to the bus in this observation. SameAs: 'stop_id' field from GTFS Realtime message-Vehicleposition (https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs-realtime/reference#message-vehicleposition)

label: stop_sequence
comment:
This field identifies the order of the stops for a particular trip. The values for stop_sequence must be non-negative integers, and they must increase along the trip.
For example, the first stop on the trip could have a stop_sequence of 1, the second stop on the trip could have a stop_sequence of 23, the third stop could have a stop_sequence of 40, and so on. SameAs: 'stop_sequence' field from GTFS Static Field definitions-stop_times.txt (https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs/reference#stop_timestxt)

label: tripDetails
comment: A descriptor of realtime update on the schedule of a vehicle along a trip.

label: trip_id
comment: Trip ID/Trip name alloted to the bus corresponding to this observation, in consideration to the time of the day and the direction of the trip on the given routeId. SameAs: 'trip_id' field from GTFS Realtime message-TripDescriptor (https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs-realtime/reference#message-tripdescriptor)

label: actualTripStartTime
comment: This field specifies the time at which service actually began.

label: vehicle_label
comment: User visible label, i.e., something that must be shown to the passenger to help identify the correct vehicle.

label: last_stop_id
comment: Stop ID/Stop name of the previous bus stop corresponding to the bus in this observation.

label: last_stop_arrival_time
comment:
Specifies the arrival time at the previous stop for a specific trip on a route. Times must be eight digits in HH:MM:SS format (H:MM:SS is also accepted, if the hour begins with 0). 
Note: Trips that span multiple dates will have stop times greater than 24:00:00. For example, if a trip begins at 10:30:00 p.m. and ends at 2:15:00 a.m. on the following day, the stop times would be 22:30:00 and 26:15:00. Entering those stop times as 22:30:00 and 02:15:00 would not produce the desired results. SameAs: 'arrival_time' field from GTFS Static Field definitions-stop_times.txt (https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs/reference#stop_timestxt)

label: latitude
comment: Current latitude position obtained from the bus/vehicle corresponding to this observation. SameAs 'latitude' from GTFS- Realtime message-Position  (https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs-realtime/reference#message-position)

label: longitude
comment: Current longitude position obtained from the bus/vehicle corresponding to this observation. SameAs 'longitude' from GTFS- Realtime message-Position  (https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs-realtime/reference#message-position)

label: speed
comment: Gives the Speed of the vehicle at the last tracked coordinates.SameAs: 'speed' field from GTFS Realtime message - Position  (https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs-realtime/reference#message-position)

label: last_tracked_time
comment: Gives the time at which the vehicle was last tracked.

label: delay
comment: This can be positive and negative in seconds and shows how much the vehicle deviates from the planned one. SameAs: 'delay' field from GTFS Realtime message-StopTimeEvent (https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs-realtime/reference#message-stoptimeevent)

label: license_plate
comment: Gives the License Plate number of the vehice. SameAs: 'license_plate' field from GTFS Realtime message-VehicleDescriptor (https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs-realtime/reference#message-vehicledescriptor)

label: tripDirection
comment: Gives the direction in which the vehicle is travelling in ENUM[UP,DN]

label: depot_id
comment: Describes the name of the bus depot corresponding to this observation.

label: seating_capacity
comment: Describes the passenger seating capacity of the vehicle corresponding to this observation.

label: standing_capacity
comment: Describes the passenger standing capacity of the vehicle corresponding to this observation.

label: ac_available
comment: Describes the presence of air conditioning option in the vehicle corresponding to this observation.
